"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by Plymouth Marine Laboratory (WSC017)&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nResponses to specific questions raised are as follows:-\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhy do numbers of women in STEM academic careers decline further up the career ladder? \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhen women leave academia, what careers do they transition into? What are the consequences of scientifically trained women applying their skills in different \nemployment sectors?\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhat should \nuniversities and the higher education sector do to retain women graduates and PhD students in academic careers? Are there examples of good practice?\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nWhat role should the Government have in encouraging the retention of women in academic STEM careers?\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nAugust 2013\n&#xa0;\n"